cription":"The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/open.png","name":"Open","id":"1","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10204","id":"10204","name":"Admin Guide"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10206","id":"10206","name":"Command Line Reference"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10203","id":"10203","name":"Installation Guide"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10205","id":"10205","name":"User Guide"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"From: Larsen, Greg (Converged Cloud) \r\nSent: Wednesday, November 18, 2015 6:03 PM\r\nTo: Burke, Michael I.; HDP tech docs; HOS tech docs; Larsen, Greg (Converged Cloud); Sofos, Dionysia; Zagorodnov, Dmitrii\r\nSubject: Changes needed to ditamaps\r\n \r\nHi,\r\n \r\nAt the hackathon this week, we got some additional requirements that we need to meet in order to make the drupal import work. I’ll be adding some checks to look for these things, and likely some additional explanation will be needed, but I wanted to get it documented and give everyone a heads up about what we need to be doing in the near future.\r\n \r\nBest regards,\r\n \r\nGreg\r\n \r\n1.       Within any given ditamap, all topic IDs for all referenced files must be unique.\r\n2.       Ditamaps may not contain any topicheads.  All entries must be topicrefs. (That is, every entry in the ditamap must reference a dita topic file)\r\n3.       Every “branch level” topic (that is, any topic that has child topics) must contain an “otherprops” attribute.  The top level topic must equal “”    The value of the attribute must be a short, lower case string that describes the branch-level and containing topics.  These strings are used construct the topic URL in Drupal  Example:\r\n\r\n  <topicref href=\"2.0/devplatform.index.dita\" navtitle=\"HPE Helion Development Platform 2.0\" locktitle=\"yes\" otherprops=\"\">\r\n    <topicref href=\"2.0/devplatform.whatsnew.dita\" locktitle=\"yes\" navtitle=\"What's New\"/>\r\n    <topicref href=\"2.0/installation/installation.dita\" navtitle=\"Installation\" otherprops=\"install\">\r\n      <topicref href=\"2.0/installation/install_offline.dita\"  navtitle=\"Downloading for Offline Installation\" locktitle=\"yes\"/>\r\n    </topicref>\r\n    <topicref href=\"2.0/monitoring/service_monitoring.dita\" navtitle=\"Service Monitoring\" otherprops=\"service-mon\">\r\n      <topicref href=\"2.0/monitoring/devplatform.messaging-monitor.dita\"/>\r\n    </topicref>\r\n    <topicref href=\"2.0/helion/CLI/cli.dita\" navtitle=\"Command Line Clients\" otherprops=\"cli\">\r\n      <topicref href=\"2.0/helion/CLI/ALS_Client_Downloads.dita\" navtitle=\"Command Line Client Downloads\" locktitle=\"yes\"/>\r\n      <topicref href=\"2.0/helion/CLI/als_helion_client.dita\" navtitle=\"ALS Helion Client\" otherprops=\"als\">\r\n        <topicref href=\"2.0/helion/user/client/client_index.dita\" locktitle=\"yes\"   navtitle=\"ALS Client Installation\"/>\r\n        <topicref href=\"2.0/helion/user/reference/client-ref.dita\" locktitle=\"yes\"    navtitle=\"ALS Client Command Reference\" otherprops=\"cli-ref\">\r\n          <topicref href=\"2.0/helion/user/reference/client-ref-administration.dita\" locktitle=\"yes\" navtitle=\"Administration\"/>\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n \r\nGreg Larsen\r\nPublications Tools Support, Converged Cloud\r\nhttp://docs.hpcloud.com \r\n ","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"Add otherprops to parent nodes in DITAmaps for Drupal","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=scottb","name":"scottb","key":"scottb","accountId":"557058:8b784f3d-4aba-42f1-a016-d04e8269968b","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Scott Butler","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"subtasks":[],"reporter":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=scottb","name":"scottb","key":"scottb","accountId":"557058:8b784f3d-4aba-42f1-a016-d04e8269968b","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/6a93de6d1d4b0053831945571f8ca4e6?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dscottb%26avatarId%3D12701%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlass